{[%evp 0,107,23,18,36,13,13,13,25,13,40,28,13,11,11,6,9,9,22,-7,-8,4,0,13,0,-9,
16,5,18,-32,2,-14,0,-2,2,5,23,14,46,45,50,54,54,45,45,47,38,43,43,43,40,36,36,
26,37,25,22,35,45,50,41,54,43,38,98,82,109,129,120,117,117,117,141,137,139,125,
112,112,130,126,137,120,151,144,158,144,172,174,187,221,216,208,208,217,225,
224,403,414,424,404,441,338,360,250,237,249,258,211,229,209]} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3
Nc6 3. Bb5 Nf6 4. O-O Nxe4 5. Re1 Nd6 6. Nxe5 Be7 7. Bf1 Nxe5 8. Rxe5 O-O 9. d4
Bf6 10. Re1 Re8 11. Rxe8+ Nxe8 12. d5 d6 13. Nd2 c6 14. Nc4 {After defeating
Aronian yesterday, Harikrishna won another technical game against the other
foreign favorite.} cxd5 15. Qxd5 {[%csl Rd6]} Qe7 {Allows time to White to
consolidate.} ({Interesting was} 15... Be6 $5 16. Qxb7 d5 17. Na5 Rc8 18. Nb3
a5 {[%cal Ga5a4,Gc8c2,Gf6a1] with compensation.}) 16. Ne3 Be6 17. Qf3 Rc8 18.
c3 Bg5 19. Nf5 Qf6 20. Bxg5 Qxg5 21. Nd4 {[%csl Rd6,Re6] There are no
weaknesses in White's camp whereas Nakamura needs to constantly worry about
his d6 isolani.} Bd5 22. Qf5 $1 {[%csl Gf5,Gg5] In the endgame the weakness is
even more visible.} Qxf5 23. Nxf5 Kf8 24. Ne3 Be6 25. a4 Nf6 26. Rd1 Ke7 (26...
Bb3 27. Rd4 {[%csl Rb3,Gb4,Rb7,Rd6][%cal Gd4b4,Gb4b7,Gb4b3,Rb3b4]}) 27. f3 Rc5
28. Rd4 a6 29. Kf2 Bd7 30. g4 $1 {[%cal Gg2g4,Gg4g5,Gh2h4,Gh4h5] Squeezing
Black from both flanks.} h5 31. h4 (31. b4 $5 {as} Rxc3 $2 {fails to} 32. g5
Ne8 33. Nd5+ {[%csl Rc3,Re7]}) 31... hxg4 32. fxg4 g5 33. h5 {There are two
wekanesses now in Black's camp-the one on d6 and the outside passer.} d5 34.
Bd3 Kf8 35. Rb4 b5 36. axb5 axb5 37. Kf3 Kg7 38. Bf5 Bc6 39. Rd4 Ne8 40. Bd3
Nc7 (40... Bd7 41. Ke2 Be6 {was more stubborn.}) 41. Nf5+ Kh8 42. Ke3 Ne6 43.
Rb4 Bd7 44. Nd6 {[%csl Rb5,Gd6,Rf7] And Black's position collapses.} Nf4 (44...
Kg7 45. Bxb5) 45. Nxf7+ Kg7 46. Nxg5 Nxd3 47. Kxd3 d4 (47... Rc4 $5 {can be
met with} 48. h6+ $1 Kxh6 49. Nf7+ Kg7 50. Ne5) 48. Rxd4 Bc8 49. Ne4 Re5 50.
Nd6 Bd7 51. Nf5+ Bxf5+ 52. gxf5 Rxf5 53. Rh4 Kh6 54. Kc2 1-0

